<doc id="865283" wikidata="Q1403248" url="?curid=865283" title="Insomniac's Dream">
<text>Insomniac&#x27;s Dream is the first EP by American rock band Adema, and was released on November 5, 2002 after their self-titled debut album. Only the first three tracks are new, though &quot;Shattered&quot; was released on some international versions of &quot;Adema&quot; and &quot;Nutshell&quot; is a cover of an Alice in Chains song. &quot;Immortal&quot; was the theme song for &quot;Mortal Kombat: Deadly Alliance&quot;, and is the only song to have had a music video.

